        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 6:43PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 643 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Mars Hills to Johns Creek. These storms were nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rain and slow to stationary storms may cause
temporary street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Marietta, Cartersville, Dallas, Cedartown, Cumming, Buchanan,
Peachtree Corners, Mountain Park, Sandy Springs, Roswell, Johns
Creek, Alpharetta, Smyrna, Dunwoody, Milton, Kennesaw, Duluth,
Woodstock, Acworth, and Sugar Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
